info.name: LA Homeless Helper API
info.description: Documentation for the LAHomelessHelper API. This API will be used to retrieve information on shelters, medicare locations, and cities within LA County.

item.name: Shelters

query.description: a string with the name of the shelter
a string with the first line of the address
a string with the second line of the address
a string with the city the shelter is located in or close to
a string with the hours of the shelter
a string with a description of a number such as "FAX" followed by a number
a string with the shelter's website URL
a double of the shelter's POST id (Peace Office Standards and Training)
a string with a short description of the shelter
a string with the shelter's zip code
a string with a link to the LA county's Location Management System
a double with the shelter's latitude
a double with the shelter's longitude
a date representing when the entry was last updated
a string with the name of the closest medicare office
a string with the 1st line of the address of the closest medicare office
a string with the 2nd line of the address of the closest medicare office
a string with the hours of the closest medicare office

request.description: Returns a JSON with a list of dictionaries. Each dictionary represents a single shelter. The dictionary has the following keys:

response.name: All Shelters

If you go past the last page, it will loop through to the first page.

item.description: Contains information on the medicare locations in LA County.

item.name: Cities

query.description: a double containing the city's alphabetical position, a unique identifier unrelated to the city
a string with the name of the city or area
a short integer representing the number of homeless people not in a shelter
a short integer representing the number of homeless people in a shelter
a short integer representing the total number of homeless people in the city or area, equal to Total_Unsheltered_Pop + Total_Sheltered_Pop
a string containing our source's source
a double representing the square miles of the city or area
a double representing the density of the unsheltered population per square mile
a double representing the density of the sheltered population per square mile
a double representing the density of homeless people per square mile
a large double seemingly unrelated to the square miles
a large double seemingly unrelated to the square miles
a string representing the name of the closest medicare office as determined by the latitude and longitude
a string representing the name of the closest shelter as determined by the latitude and longitude
